<heading id="D0EE81A6FFDC8B055E8FFE1E22A8FE0E" bold="true" box="[189,457,396,422]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055E8FFE1E22A8FE0E" bold="true" box="[189,457,396,422]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFDC8B055E8FFE2822C1FDCA" blockId="47.[189,1399,442,610]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055E8FFE2822D3FE7C" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[189,434,442,468]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055E8FFE2822D3FE7C" box="[189,434,442,468]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ebenacobius atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFDC8B055F8CFE29214DFE7D" box="[446,556,443,469]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by the combination of appendiculate claws and elytra with distinct but recumbent setae, as long as or shorter than width of interstriae. This species is very close to, if not a synonym of, 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055C4EFD90218CFDB3" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[636,749,514,539]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turneri" status="gen. et comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055C4EFD90218CFDB3" box="[636,749,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. turneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFDC8B055CC4FD9320B0FDB3" box="[758,977,513,539]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see the remarks section under that species). 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055F18FDB722FCFD96" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[298,413,549,574]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055F18FDB722FCFD96" box="[298,413,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short, not or slightly raised squamiform setae on elytra (long, erect and piliform setae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055F2FFDDA22EEFDC9" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[285,399,584,609]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turneri">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055F2FFDDA22EEFDC9" box="[285,399,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. turneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
