<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFDC8B055E8FFCD8226EFB9F" blockId="47.[188,1401,842,1080]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055E8FFCD822CFFCCC" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[189,430,842,868]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055E8FFCD822CFFCCC" box="[189,430,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ebenacobius atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFDC8B055F84FCD92140FCCD" box="[438,545,843,869]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) was described in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055D42FCD82091FCCC" authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1825" box="[880,1008,842,868]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055D42FCD82091FCCC" box="[880,1008,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Derelomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single male deposited at SAMC (
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B3BFFDC8B055F08FCFC22A6FC20" author="Hesse J. C." box="[314,455,878,904]" firstAuthor="Hesse" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="475 - 536" part="25" refId="ref30885" refString="Hesse J. C. 1929. Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa. Annals of the South African Museum 25: 475 - 536." title="Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa" type="journal article" year="1929">
<collectingRegion id="49DDF828FFDC8B055F08FCFC22E3FC20" box="[314,386,878,904]" country="Germany" name="Hessen" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Hesse</collectingRegion>
1929
</bibRefCitation>
). This specimen was loaned to Guillermo Kuschel (loan 24018) who undertook a study on palaeotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055FE1FC032138FC03" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[467,601,913,939]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
from 2007. Unfortunately he passed away before he could complete this work and left the very preliminary manuscript and the material borrowed from institutions was partly not recovered (see postscript in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B3BFFDC8B055CBFFC4A2004FC59" author="Haran J. &amp; Beaudoin-Ollivier L. &amp; Benoit L. &amp; Kuschel G." box="[653,869,983,1010]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Haran" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 32" part="684" refId="ref30703" refString="Haran J., Beaudoin-Ollivier L., Benoit L. &amp; Kuschel G. 2020. Revision of the palm-pollinating weevil genus Elaeidobius Kuschel, 1952 (Curculionidae, Curculioninae, Derelomini) with descriptions of two new species. European Journal of Taxonomy 684: 1 - 32. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2020.684" title="Revision of the palm-pollinating weevil genus Elaeidobius Kuschel, 1952 (Curculionidae, Curculioninae, Derelomini) with descriptions of two new species" type="journal article" year="2020">
Haran 
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFDC8B055CD3FC4A207FFC59" box="[737,798,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Despite intensive search in the material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFDC8B055E8DFC682224FBBC" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1865" box="[191,325,1018,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Derelomini">Derelomini</taxonomicName>
loaned, the 
<typeStatus id="54A28868FFDC8B055FE5FC68215FFBBC" box="[471,574,1018,1044]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species could not be identified and is provisionally considered as lost.
</paragraph>
